## 11) Delivery Plan (Phased)

### Phase 1 - Foundation (Week 1)
- Fork scaffold foundation into Speak Draft app shell
- Rename branding/routes/components
- Implement workspace/user/role schema
- Wire auth and protected/private route model

### Phase 2 - Core Content Flow (Week 2-3)
- Brief CRUD and phase tracker
- Interview token generation + guest room shell
- Transcript ingest and storage
- Draft generation pipeline with status transitions

### Phase 3 - HubSpot and Billing (Week 3-4)
- Workspace HubSpot OAuth connect
- Draft push to HubSpot (DRAFT state)
- Workspace credits + ledger + blocking rules
- Polar webhook integration with workspace credit allocation

### Phase 4 - Hardening and Readiness (Week 4)
- Security checklist closure
- Rate limits and retry behavior
- QA against publish-ready rubric
- Pre-ship review and smoke tests

---

## 12) Acceptance Criteria (MVP)

MVP is complete when:
1. Admin can create workspace, invite member, connect HubSpot.
2. Member can create brief, run interview, generate draft.
3. Draft can be reviewed/approved and pushed to HubSpot as draft.
4. Credits are deducted accurately and never go negative.
5. Workspace isolation is verified.
6. Guest link expiry and single-use behavior are enforced.
7. Major error paths are observable in Sentry.

